PN,41501
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1777295491
OL,3,CHMS Victory masts to be removed as
OL,4,Cpart of #42 million conservation
OL,5,Cproject
OL,7,FThe masts from Vice-Admiral Lord
OL,8,FNelson's flagship HMS Victory are to
OL,9,Fbe removed in the latest stage of a
OL,10,F#42 million conservation project.
OL,12,FA 750-tonne crane will lift the mizzen
OL,13,F(rear), foremast (front) and bowsprit
OL,14,F(bow), and lay it by the side of the
OL,15,F18th century warship at Portsmouth
OL,16,FHistoric Dockyard.
OL,18,FThe removals, which will begin on
OL,19,FMonday evening, come after the main
OL,20,Fmast was removed in 2021 as part of
OL,21,Fthe project.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
